-- Monti Says Italy to Meet EU Budget Rules After Vote, Ansa Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 2012-10-24T12:04:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/monti-says-italy-to-meet-eu-budget-rules-after-vote-ansa-says.html
Italian Prime Minister  Mario Monti 
said the next government, which will be installed after the
parliamentary elections required by the end of April, will
respect European Union budget rules, according to Ansa.  “Thank you for all the expressions of esteem, especially
in recent weeks, but please relax,” Monti told reporters in
Rome, Ansa said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Andrew Frye in Milan at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net . 